<section>
  <h2>Rush</h2>
  <p><strong>Week One: </strong>Sigma Phi Delta brothers will be boothing at the Resource Fair as well as the Dexter lawn area. Feel free to drop by and meet some of us and pick up a flyer of events. We will be recruiting for our fraternity's rush that starts the following week.</p>
  <p><strong>Week Two: </strong>Rush week begins and ends. Each day there will be a different event set up for Cal Poly students to come and get to know the brothers. This week is also our chance to meet people who we will potentially invite to join Sigma Phi Delta. The details of these events are listed below:</p>
  <p><strong>Day One: Info Session</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Time: 6 - 8 PM on Monday, Sept. 28th</li>
    <li>Location: Baker Science (180), room 102</li>
    <li>Hear a presentation given by our rush chairman, Garrett Chan, and meet and greet with brothers and fellow rushees. Food will be provided.</li>
  </ul>
  <p><strong>Day Two: Dinner at Sylvester's</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Time: 6 - 9 PM on Tuesday, Sept. 29th</li>
    <li>Location: the PAC</li>
    <li>Rushees will meet at the PAC at 6 PM, where brothers of SPD will then give rides to Sylvester's in Los Osos. Delicious burgers and food comas await attendees.</li>
  </ul>
  <p><strong>Day Three: Sports Day</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Time: 6 - 8 PM on Wednesday, Sept. 30th</li>
    <li>Location: in front of the Rec Center</li>
    <li>Ultimate frisbee is what's in store for anyone who dare challenge the brothers at sports day. Depending on demand, basketball is also an agenda item. Come hang out and show off your athleticism!</li>
  </ul>
  <p><strong>Day Four: Resume Workshop and Game Night</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Time: 6 - 9 PM on Thursday, Oct. 1st</li>
    <li>Location: Graphic Arts (26), room 103</li>
    <li>This is the chance to get your resume in shape and prepared for the career fair. Fellow engineers in the brotherhood will help you tune your resume and skills to what is important to your specific major. This is a really good networking opportunity.</li>
  </ul>
  <p><strong>The Weekend: </strong>Be sure to keep Friday and Saturday open for fraternity purposes. If you are selected to join, these will be important days.</p>
  <p><strong>Please direct any questions to Recruitment Chairman Garrett Chan: recruitment.spd.calpoly@gmail.com</strong></p>
